Hannah Montana - The Movie(2009)

Hannah Montana: The Movie is a 2009 American musical film adaptation of American teen sitcom Hannah Montana. The movie tells of how Hannah Montana's popularity begins to take over Miley Stewart's life. Miley's father forces her to take a trip to her hometown of Crowley Corners, Tennessee to get some perspective on what matters the most in her life.

High School Musical (January 20, 2006)

High School Musical was Disney Channel's most watched movie that year with 7.7 million viewers in its premiere broadcast in the US. In the UK, it received 789,000 viewers for its premiere (and 1.2 million viewers overall during the first week), making it the second most watched program for the Disney Channel (UK) of 2006. On December 29, 2006, it became the first Disney Channel Original Movie to be broadcast on the BBC. Globally, High School Musical has been seen by over 225 million viewers.

Cast

Troy Bolton (Zac Efron) is the main protagonist of the film.

Gabriella Montez (Vanessa Anne Hudgens) is one of the braniacs on the scholastic decathlon team.

Sharpay Evans (Ashley Tisdale) is the antagonist of the film.

Chad Danforth (Corbin Bleu) is Troy's best friend.

Ryan Evans (Lucas Grabeel) is Sharpay's twin brother.

Taylor McKessie (Monique Coleman) is Gabriella's best friend.She is captain of the school Scholastic Decathlon team.

Jack Bolton (Bart Johnson) is Troy's father and the coach of the basketball team.

Ms. Darbus (Alyson Reed) is the stern drama teacher at East High.

Kelsi Nielsen (Olesya Rulin) is a student at East High. She is a pianist and composer.

Zeke Baylor (Chris Warren, Jr.) is friends with Troy and Chad.

Jason Cross (Ryne Sanborn) is friends with Troy and Chad. He also tends to ask silly questions in class.

The Last Song (2010)

The Last Song is a 2010 American coming-of-age drama film developed alongside the Nicholas Sparks novel by the same name. The Last Song stars Miley Cyrus, Liam Hemsworth, Greg Kinnear, and Bobby Coleman and follows a troubled teenager as she reconnects with her estranged father and falls in love during a summer in a quiet Southern United States beach town.

Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam (June 25, 2010)- I can't wait to see it!

Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam is an upcoming 2010 Disney Channel Original Movie and the sequel to Camp Rock. It was filmed all around Toronto, Ontario.Production for the film began in September 2009. It will premiere on July 30, 2010, as seen on Disney Channel.
